# FileMind AI - System Architecture & Workflow Documentation

Welcome to the official technical architecture and workflow specification for **FileMind AI**—a premium, local LLM-powered intelligence system designed to scan, analyze, index, and report on files, logs, images, and folders natively on your local CPU.

This document provides a comprehensive technical overview of the system architecture, memory subsystems, data flow pipelines, component schemas, and engineering milestones achieved throughout this project.

---

## 1. High-Level System Architecture

FileMind AI is engineered around a modular, low-latency pipeline that processes user queries, routes intents, interacts with persistent vector databases and sliding conversational memory, runs localized domain-specific file analyzers, and streams results in real time.

```mermaid
graph TD
    User([USER]) -->|Natural Language Input| Main[main.py]
    
    %% Intent Routing
    Main -->|Detect Intent| Router[utils/intent_router.py]
    Router -->|General Chat / Question| GenBlock[General AI Block]
    Router -->|Direct File/Folder Path| AnalyzeBlock[Analysis Router Block]
    Router -->|Report Generation Command| ReportBlock[Report Generation Block]
    
    %% Memory Integration
    GenBlock -->|Fetch Context| MemoryEngine[ai/ai_engine.py]
    AnalyzeBlock -->|Scan Target| Analyzers[analyzers/*]
    
    %% Local LLM
    MemoryEngine -->|Query Vector Store| DB[(ChromaDB Vector Memory)]
    MemoryEngine -->|Query Conversational Store| Cache[(conversation_history.json)]
    MemoryEngine -->|Send Isolated or Compiled Prompt| LLM[Llama Cpp / DeepSeek Coder 6.7B]
    
    %% Output
    LLM -->|Stream UTF-8 Output| User
    
    %% Report & Persistent State
    ReportBlock -->|Load Active Project Target| StateManager[reports/active_project.json]
    ReportBlock -->|Trigger Analysis & Compile| ReportGen[report_generator/report_generator.py]
    ReportGen -->|Save Premium Markdown Report| Disk[(Disk / User Directory)]
```

