## 2. Dynamic Data & Control Workflows

### 2.1 The Conversational Chat Pipeline
When the user submits a normal conversational query (e.g. *"Explain what machine learning is simply"*), the system executes the following data lifecycle:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as USER
    participant Main as main.py
    participant Router as intent_router.py
    participant Engine as ai_engine.py
    participant ConvMem as conversation_memory.py
    participant DB as persistent_memory.py (ChromaDB)
    participant LLM as DeepSeek Coder (llama.cpp)

    User->>Main: Enter Input ("Explain it in exactly 2 lines")
    Main->>Router: detect_intent(text)
    Note over Router: Checks for disk paths or report commands
    Router-->>Main: Returns intent {"type": "general"}
    Main->>Engine: ask_ai_stream(text, save_to_memory=True)
    
    par Query Conversational Context
        Engine->>ConvMem: get_instruct_context()
        ConvMem-->>Engine: Returns sliding chat history list
    and Query Semantic Memory
        Engine->>DB: search_memory(text)
        Note over DB: Computes cosine similarity over CPU embeddings
        DB-->>Engine: Returns relevant prior contexts
    end

    Engine->>Engine: Compile Prompt (System Instructions + Memories + History + Query)
    Engine->>LLM: Stream Inference (Temperature=0.7, n_ctx=12288)
    LLM-->>User: UTF-8 Stream Emojis & Text directly to Console stdout
    LLM-->>Engine: Complete Response String
    
    par Commit Conversational Turn
        Engine->>ConvMem: add_message("assistant", response)
        Note over ConvMem: Saves turn to conversation_history.json
    and Embed Persistent Memory
        Engine->>DB: store_memory(turn_text)
        Note over DB: Embeds and saves to ChromaDB SQLite index
    end
```

